SOURCE CELL SUSPENSION ID: The unique Cell suspension ID of the cell suspension this sequence file was derived from.
READ INDEX (Required): The sequencing read this file represents.
LANE INDEX: The lane that this file was sequenced from.
READ LENGTH: The length of a sequenced read in this file, in nucleotides.
INSDC RUN ACCESSION: An INSDC (International Nucleotide Sequence Database Collaboration) run accession from the DDBJ, NCBI, or EMBL-EBI.
INSDC EXPERIMENT ACCESSION: An International Nucleotide Sequence Database Collaboration (INSDC) experiment accession.
LIBRARY PREPARATION ID: A unique ID for the library preparation.
LIBRARY PREPARATION PROTOCOL ID: An ID of a Library preparation protocol used to generate this file.
SEQUENCING PROTOCOL ID: An ID of a Sequencing protocol used to generate this file.
PROCESS ID: A unique ID for the process.

FILE NAME (Required): Include the file extension in the file name. For example: R1.fastq.gz; codebook.json
SOURCE CELL SUSPENSION ID: Use a Cell suspension ID you already provided in the Cell suspension Tab.
FILE FORMAT (Required): Indicate the full file extension including compression extensions. For example: fastq.gz; tif
READ INDEX (Required): If a sequencing experiment is single-end, enter 'read1'. For example: Should be one of: read1, read2, index1, index2
INSDC RUN ACCESSION: Accession must start with DRR, SRR, or ERR. For example: SRR0000000
INSDC EXPERIMENT ACCESSION: Enter accession if experiment has been archived. Accession can be from the DDBJ, NCBI, or EMBL-EBI and must start with DRX, SRX, or ERX, respecitvely. For example: SRX0000000
LIBRARY PREPARATION ID: Indicate which samples are from the same library preparation by providing a unique identifier for each library preparation. For example: tech_rep_group_001
LIBRARY PREPARATION PROTOCOL ID: Use a Library preparation protocol ID you provided in the Library preparation protocol Tab.
SEQUENCING PROTOCOL ID: Use a Sequencing protocol ID you provided in the Sequencing protocol Tab.

FILE NAME (Required): FILL OUT INFORMATION BELOW THIS ROW
